The paper deals with video object segmentation, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning spatio-temporal features self-adapting to the object of interest, which suggests the use of machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents results on the DAVIS dataset, which is a benchmark for video object segmentation (cs.MM).
